<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1367] Add a isDeleted method to IndexCommit</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1367</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;I wish to add a IndexCommit.isDeleted() method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The use-case is that Solr will now support configurable IndexDeletionPolicy (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-617&quot; title=&quot;Allow configurable deletion policy&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-617&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). For the new replication (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-561&quot; title=&quot;Solr replication by Solr (for windows also)&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-561&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) to work, we need access to a list of IndexCommit instances which haven&apos;t been deleted yet. I can wrap the user specified IndexDeletionPolicy but since the IndexCommit does not have a isDeleted method, I may store a reference to an IndexCommit on which delete() has been called by the deletion policy. I can wrap the IndexCommit objects too just for having a isDeleted() method so a workaround exists. Not a big pain but if it can be managed on the lucene side easily, I&apos;ll appreciate it. It would save me from writing some delegate code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
